  "text": "Based on the intensity of protein bands shown in Figure 4 , it can be tentatively concluded that there are low molecular weight (fractions III, IV, V and VI) and high molecular weight (fractions I and II) protein in roselle seed. The high molecular weight (fraction I) of roselle protein was found in native PAGE (N1), but not in SDS PAGE (S1). The major fractions detected in native PAGE are I and II, while in SDS PAGE are III and VI. Heating prior to SDS-PAGE was highly likely to dissociate the high molecular weight into lower molecular weight subunits [CITATION_1] . The high molecular weight fractions (I and II) in native PAGE may largely correspond to globulin as proposed by [CITATION_2] . Other fractions with low molecular weight in roselle protein represent albumin and glutelin.",
